data.chStory: Sithrak is a Murder Elf Doom prophet, accidentally turned into a Lich by the Rites of Perfect Creation. He is a relentless champion for slaughter, battle and song.
A rogue magical entity returned to Elgardt from time in the Shadow Realm with friend

i am a wizard from another world while traveling the multiverse i lost my map and dimensional travel stone i am now trapped in Elgardt. I wish to Learn many things Before traveling back to my home plain everon.
See Wiki Page

After Blaarg escaped child experimentation, by poisoning her captor and her magic manifested, she made her way to Hamaglen, where Zorg invited her to join the Chain Breakers and she soon inherited the role of Shaman. The horde moved to Aylet where Blaarg quickly rose in notoriety and self-delusion.

Born poor to a family in the Mattahon, Uthil was destined for little - even life as an oarsmen was denied him, owing to a severe case of seasickness. All but abandoned, he was 'adopted' by a passing regiment of Free Companions, one of the roving bands of rogues and cutthroats who fight for any who could pay. He grew up with them, travelling the world, making friends in odd places and learning some 'interesting' skills.nnNow adrift, owing to his company's near destruction at the hands of a traitorous employer, he has found himself in Aylet seeking employment and other... diversions. Skilled with a bow and handy with a blade, he has few issues with his line of work, seeing it as merely a living.
A monk from the order of *Insert good aligned deity*. A man that previously had quite a sheltered life and wants to see the world for himself and make it a better place.
To be filled in later

Felwynn is a travelling paladin initiate, out to see the world and make a name for herself. Young, reckless and untested, what she lacks in martial prowess, she makes up for in faith and optimism. Recently been inducted into the Luminous Order.
Loren was a lost human child raised by wolves who then sold him into Orcish slavery for 2 steaks and a scratch under the chin...
You can call me 'rung for short
An ex-thug raised by circumstance; now acts as the bodyguard to Mirabella
Tbc
A traveler from distant stars
A human ranger who came out of obscurity, there is nothing particularly notable about him. He on a whim came to the city of Aylet, where he now sells his skills as a tracker and master ranger.

An out cast tho unaware of it, Mask came crashing into the world through a pothole in which a giant Wyrm was spotted that he was on which he fell off seen by a practicing Mage from the Arcane University this old dwarven Mage Gregor adopted him into the University Arcana and treated him like a son. A half breed known as a Dwelf. Half dwarf and half elf. Suffering from Majour Amnesia he did not know anything before he came through this porthole, not even his own name, infact he had no idea why he had a mask on nor did he understand why he had armour on with strange markings on its inner surface. Nor did he know his mother or father. But he came to adopt the nick name people called him. Mask. As a cheaky rebellious  practisioner of magic, he did learn some of the darker arts in secret by a Dark arts Mage known as Abhorsen. As well as his lighter arts of magic taught to him by his adopted farther Gregor.

Vail crossed the sea in search of his two older brothers (Va and Vass). The three brothers were meant to become the holy men of his clan (Greystone) but part way into the ritual they came under attack from foreign Invaders they either slaughtered or enslaved everyone at the ritual if not for the unearthly power of the storms that plague the obsidian sea vail would of suffered the same fate as his brother, now in an unknown land with nothing but the cloths of the dead apon his back and the family ring vail will stop at nothing to find his brothers to either save them or send their souls off to Odis (His God).n

An interdimensional rogue scholar, originally from Phase World, was attempting to access the Hell Dimension to aid a group of powerful beings in preventing the spread of the fiendish Yama Kings. Unfortunately, his interdimensional breaching device went haywire and dumped him in Elgard. Trapped alone without his gear he must now go about finding a way back home.

Dave grew up as the apprentice of his father the master blacksmith at Fort Hamaglen. As a child he would train with heavy armour and shields accompanied by his mentor Sir Jonah (sir Jon, to Dave), who was influential in his early life. When the time came for him to assume the mantle of his father's position, he took to the opportunity but soon fell out of favour. He found himself on the run after he found he had insulted the steward while drunk. False charges were raised against him, but dave caught wind of them with thanks to the faithful maid Mildred and he escaped in the dead of night. Dave roamed the country for a time, but eventually he came to reside in Ayelet. Here, he swore himself against alcohol and refuses to enter or go near taverns, and swore himself to aid those in need. (Dave is fairly swayed by social pressure).

A dwarf lion shifter travelling from the north in searching for sellsword work and bountied to collect, armed with his two trusty blades and a silver tong as he travels the world looking looking for the next story to be told.
